vectorData.altText: That's right!  The biceps femoris tendon is labelled ’B’. This hamstring muscle borders the superolateral border of the popliteal fossa.

The popliteal fossa provides the major route by which structures pass between the thigh and the leg. It is a diamond-shaped regions posterior to the knee, analogous to the cubital fossa in the upper limb.

and place it prone on the table. Identify the muscular borders of the popliteal fossa. Identify the hamstring muscles forming its borders superomedially and superolaterally. Identify, forming its inferomedial and inferolateral borders, the medial and lateral heads of the gastrocnemius muscle, respectively. Identify, forming its floor, the fibrous capsule of the knee joint, the popliteal surface of the femur and the posterior aspect of the proximal tibia.
